                "invention-title": [
                    "Liquid gallium metal and hollow glass microsphere composite hydrogen storage material",
                    "液态金属镓和中空玻璃微球复合储氢材料"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to a liquid metal gallium and hollow glass microsphere composite hydrogen storage material. According to the material, glass microspheres are etched through dilute hydrofluoric acid, so that defects are generated on the surfaces of the glass microspheres, and then the glass microspheres are mixed and stirred with liquid metal gallium to form gallium-coated glass microsphere composite powder. The material realizes efficient hydrogen storage under mild conditions, and the hydrogen storage density meets various application requirements. The preparation method is simple and suitable for large-scale production. The hydrogen storage density of the composite hydrogen storage material is 1.61 wt% and 3.14 wt% respectively at the temperature of 100 DEG C and 200 DEG C under the hydrogen pressure of 5 MPa. Liquid metal gallium effectively reduces reaction energy barriers of hydrogen molecule cracking and hydrogen atom recombination, and hydrogen storage dynamics and thermodynamics are improved. The composite hydrogen storage material Ga-coated HGMs provided by the invention has excellent performance, provides a new solution for the field of hydrogen storage, and is expected to play an important role in fixed and movable hydrogen storage devices. In addition, due to the considerable hydrogen storage capacity and rapid adsorption kinetics of the material, the material has remarkable advantages in practical application, and the development of a hydrogen storage technology is expected to be promoted."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及一种液态金属镓和中空玻璃微球复合储氢材料。该材料通过稀氢氟酸刻蚀玻璃微球，使其表面产生缺陷，随后与液态金属镓混合搅拌，形成镓涂附的玻璃微球复合粉末。此材料在温和条件下实现高效氢气存储，储氢密度满足多种应用需求。制备方法简单，适用于大规模生产。复合储氢材料在100℃和200℃、5MPa氢气压力下，分别实现1.61wt％和3.14wt％的储氢密度。液态金属镓有效降低氢气分子裂解和氢原子重组的反应能垒，改善储氢动力学和热力学。该发明提供的复合储氢材料Ga@HGMs具有优异性能，为氢气储存领域提供新的解决方案，有望在固定式和移动式储氢装置中发挥重要作用。此外，该材料的可观储氢容量和快速吸附动力学使其在实际应用中具有显著优势，有望推动氢气储存技术的发展。"
                }
            ]
